title: Google\Cloud\ServiceDirectory\V1beta1\Endpoint
name: Endpoint
description:
An individual endpoint that provides a [service][google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1beta1.Service]. The service must already exist to create an endpoint.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1beta1.Endpoint

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Immutable. The resource name for the endpoint in the format 'projects/*/locations/*/namespaces/*/services/*/endpoints/*'.

params.name: data.address
params.description: Optional. An IPv4 or IPv6 address. Service Directory will reject bad addresses like: "8.8.8" "8.8.8.8:53" "test:bad:address" "[::1]" "[::1]:8080" Limited to 45 characters.

params.name: data.port
params.description: Optional. Service Directory will reject values outside of [0, 65535].

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: Optional. Metadata for the endpoint. This data can be consumed by service clients. The entire metadata dictionary may contain up to 512 characters, spread accoss all key-value pairs. Metadata that goes beyond any these limits will be rejected.
